<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="508" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1533,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1534,1560]" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length 13.6; total width 6.6; head length 1.4; head width 3.0; interocular distance: 1.6; length of antennomeres I: 0.9; II: 0.7; III: 1.4; IV: 2.5; V: lost; pronotum length 2.6; pronotum width 7.7; scutellum length 5.7; scutellum width 4.4.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="508" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1533,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1641,1667]" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Second antennomer smaller than the others (II&lt;I&lt;III&lt;IV).Anterolateral margin of pronotum punctured (
<figureCitation box="[159,262,1678,1704]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[365,1220,179,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-44@15.[179,1412,151,1930]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B Hypoxys myrtacivorus sp. n.; C–D H. striatus sp. n.; E–F H. saltensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911532/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Fig. 10E</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with punctures of the same size (
<figureCitation box="[780,883,1678,1704]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[365,1220,179,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-44@15.[179,1412,151,1930]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B Hypoxys myrtacivorus sp. n.; C–D H. striatus sp. n.; E–F H. saltensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911532/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Fig. 10E</figureCitation>
). Hemelytrom membrane transparent (
<figureCitation box="[1321,1424,1678,1704]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[365,1220,179,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-44@15.[179,1412,151,1930]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B Hypoxys myrtacivorus sp. n.; C–D H. striatus sp. n.; E–F H. saltensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911532/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Fig. 10E</figureCitation>
). Metasternal process with arms of anterior bifurcation receiving 2/3 of third rostral segment (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1258,1714,1740]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[365,1220,179,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-44@15.[179,1412,151,1930]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B Hypoxys myrtacivorus sp. n.; C–D H. striatus sp. n.; E–F H. saltensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911532/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Fig. 10F</figureCitation>
). Pseudosutures of abdomen without adjacent dark green spot (
<figureCitation box="[672,772,1750,1776]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[365,1220,179,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-44@15.[179,1412,151,1930]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B Hypoxys myrtacivorus sp. n.; C–D H. striatus sp. n.; E–F H. saltensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911532/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Fig. 10F</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[792,969,1749,1776]" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Dorsal surface with spot extending about ½ of the length of the pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[535,625,1786,1812]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1427,1451]" captionTargetBox="[164,1409,212,1354]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[151,1435,181,1403]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys saltensis sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911509/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Dorsal rim with lateral expansions level with posterolateral angles and rounded (
<figureCitation box="[257,402,1822,1848]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1427,1451]" captionTargetBox="[164,1409,212,1354]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[151,1435,181,1403]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys saltensis sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911509/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Figs. 3A, 3C</figureCitation>
). Superior process of the genital cup elliptic, face rough in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[1225,1311,1822,1848]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1427,1451]" captionTargetBox="[164,1409,212,1354]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[151,1435,181,1403]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys saltensis sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911509/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Paramere spearhead-shaped, lobes slightly developed, apex truncated (
<figureCitation box="[837,987,1858,1884]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1427,1451]" captionTargetBox="[164,1409,212,1354]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[151,1435,181,1403]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys saltensis sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911509/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Figs. 3B, 3D</figureCitation>
). Proctiger strongly excavated laterally, excavation covered by long and dense setae; dorsal face tapering posteriorly; posterior face subpentagonal, basal third constricted (
<figureCitation box="[347,493,1930,1956]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1427,1451]" captionTargetBox="[164,1409,212,1354]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[151,1435,181,1403]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys saltensis sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911509/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Figs. 3B, 3D</figureCitation>
). Inner wall with swollen area large and close to posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation box="[1277,1365,1930,1956]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1427,1451]" captionTargetBox="[164,1409,212,1354]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[151,1435,181,1403]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypoxys saltensis sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911509/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
, black arrow). Ventral rim strongly excavated, U-shaped; expansions ending laterally in a rounded projection (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1424,1966,1992]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[201,1400,209,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1435,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys curvatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911514/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,355,2001,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="508">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
