share the proctiger strongly laterally excavated and tapered posteriorly. The species 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[888,1020,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saltensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[888,1020,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">H. saltensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1029,1094,223,249]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1029,1094,223,249]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from the other species of the group 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes et al." authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Dallas" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[297,471,258,285]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[297,471,258,285]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">H. triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by anterior and posterior lobes of the paramere barely developed, giving a spearhead shape.
</paragraph>
